## More Than Just Variables

The `${ }` block essentially creates a mini JavaScript execution window perfectly cut into your string.

You can put actual math or logic expressions *inside* the injection block, and it will execute immediately before printing!

```javascript
let price = 10;
let qty = 5;

// It does the math dynamically inside the string!
console.log(`Your total is $${price * qty} today!`);
```

